\pard\sa220\sb260\f0\fs34\b\cf2 11. What changes appear automatically and what need a code push\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa180\sb180\f0\fs26\b\cf2 Changes that appear automatically after publishing in Sanity\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab new blog articles\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab edits to blog article copy\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab new About sections\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab edits to About section copy\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab image changes inside those supported content types\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab reordering About sections through `Order`\par
\par
\pard\sa180\sb180\f0\fs26\b\cf2 Changes that still need code edits and a push\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab layout changes\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab spacing changes\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab navigation changes\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab footer changes\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab homepage hero copy\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab blog landing hero copy\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab About landing hero copy\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab new page types\par
\par
\pard\sa220\sb260\f0\fs34\b\cf2 12. How to push code to production\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 Run:\par
\par
\pard\sa180\li360\ri360\cbpat1\cf5\f1\fs19
cd "/Users/benmurr/Documents/New project"\line 
git status\line 
git add .\line 
git commit -m "Describe the change"\line 
git push\line 
\par\pard\cf0\f0\fs24
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 Then:\par
\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 1.\tab Wait a minute or two\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 2.\tab Let Vercel redeploy\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 3.\tab Refresh the live site\par
\par
\pard\sa220\sb260\f0\fs34\b\cf2 13. Beginner troubleshooting\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa180\sb180\f0\fs26\b\cf2 Problem: localhost is not loading\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 Make sure the local server is running.\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 For the website:\par
\par
\pard\sa180\li360\ri360\cbpat1\cf5\f1\fs19
npm run dev\line 
\par\pard\cf0\f0\fs24
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 For Sanity:\par
\par
\pard\sa180\li360\ri360\cbpat1\cf5\f1\fs19
npx sanity@latest dev --port 3333\line 
\par\pard\cf0\f0\fs24
\par
\pard\sa180\sb180\f0\fs26\b\cf2 Problem: the wrong localhost port appears\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 Sometimes `3000` is already in use and Next starts on `3001`.\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 Either:\par
\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab use the new port shown in Terminal\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab or stop the old process and restart\par
\par
\pard\sa180\sb180\f0\fs26\b\cf2 Problem: content is published in Sanity but not visible on the site\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 Check:\par
\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 1.\tab the entry is actually published\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 2.\tab the slug is correct\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 3.\tab the content type is supported by the page\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 4.\tab the page has been refreshed\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 5.\tab you allow a short delay for revalidation\par
\par
\pard\sa180\sb180\f0\fs26\b\cf2 Problem: new About section is in the wrong place\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 Check the `Order` field in Sanity.\par
\par
\pard\sa180\sb180\f0\fs26\b\cf2 Problem: I changed something but the live site did not update\b0\cf0\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 Ask:\par
\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab was this a content change in Sanity\par
\pard\sa120\li360\fi-180\f0\fs22 \\u8226?\tab or a code/layout change\par
\par
\pard\sa180\f0\fs24 If it was a code/layout change, it needs a Git push.\par
\par
\pard\sa220\sb260\f0\fs34\b\cf2 14. Recommended working pattern\b0\cf0\par
\par
